WHO   — The Punch-Dance — grief turned to motion
WHAT  — The most honest scene in disguise: rage and grief processed not in dialogue but in pure absurd motion.
WHERE — HRD · Hot Rod (2007)  Framework inputs: Hot Rod (2007, dir. Akiva Schaffer, The Lonely Island/Paramount); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the comedy won't let anyone say the feeling, so the body does it — and that's the parable's emotional core.
HOW   — By turning a man's lowest moment into a Footloose freak-out that feels everything the script won't speak.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the feeling the movie won't say out loud. Rod can't talk it, so he dances it — and that's the truest thing in here.

